-- Magnitude 6.6 quake hits southwest Nicaragua - USGS
-- 
-- Fri Apr 11, 2014 04:45PM EDT
-- None



MANAGUA, April 11 (Reuters) - A 6.6 magnitude earthquake hit southwest Nicaragua on Friday near the coast, the U.S. Geological Survey said, shaking buildings in the capital Managua and as far away as San Jose in Costa Rica.

There were no immediate details on any damage.